@startuml sell-domain-sequence
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFF0
  BorderColor #CCCCAA
}

title Domain Sequence Diagram: Sell 12 Shares of AAPL @ 150.00 (Gherkin Scenario 2)

participant "Application\nService" as Service #LightBlue
participant "Portfolio\n(Aggregate Root)" as Portfolio #LightGreen
participant "Holding\n(Entity)\nTicker: AAPL" as Holding #LightYellow
participant "Lot #1\n(Entity)\nShares: 10 @ 100.00" as Lot1 #Wheat
participant "Lot #2\n(Entity)\nShares: 5 @ 120.00" as Lot2 #Wheat

Service -> Portfolio: sell(Ticker("AAPL"), ShareQuantity(12), Price(150.00))
activate Service
activate Portfolio

Portfolio -> Portfolio: validate quantity.isPositive() ✓
Portfolio -> Portfolio: check holdings.containsKey(Ticker("AAPL")) ✓

Portfolio -> Holding: sell(ShareQuantity(12), Price(150.00))
activate Holding

Holding -> Holding: check getTotalShares() ≥ 12\n(10 + 5 = 15 ≥ 12) ✓

note over Holding
  **FIFO Algorithm starts**
  remainingToSell = ShareQuantity(12)
  costBasis = Money.ZERO
end note

== FIFO Step 1: Lot #1 (oldest) ==

Holding -> Holding: sharesSoldFromLot =\nmin(ShareQuantity(10), ShareQuantity(12))\n= ShareQuantity(10)

Holding -> Lot1: calculateCostBasis(ShareQuantity(10))
activate Lot1
Lot1 -> Lot1: Price(100.00) × 10 = Money(1000.00)
Lot1 --> Holding: Money(1000.00)
deactivate Lot1

Holding -> Lot1: reduce(ShareQuantity(10))
activate Lot1
Lot1 -> Lot1: remainingShares =\nShareQuantity(10) − ShareQuantity(10)\n= ShareQuantity(0)
Lot1 --> Holding
deactivate Lot1

Holding -> Holding: costBasis = Money(0) + Money(1000.00)\n= Money(1000.00)\nremainingToSell = ShareQuantity(12) − ShareQuantity(10)\n= ShareQuantity(2)

== FIFO Step 2: Lot #2 (next oldest) ==

Holding -> Holding: sharesSoldFromLot =\nmin(ShareQuantity(5), ShareQuantity(2))\n= ShareQuantity(2)

Holding -> Lot2: calculateCostBasis(ShareQuantity(2))
activate Lot2
Lot2 -> Lot2: Price(120.00) × 2 = Money(240.00)
Lot2 --> Holding: Money(240.00)
deactivate Lot2

Holding -> Lot2: reduce(ShareQuantity(2))
activate Lot2
Lot2 -> Lot2: remainingShares =\nShareQuantity(5) − ShareQuantity(2)\n= ShareQuantity(3)
Lot2 --> Holding
deactivate Lot2

Holding -> Holding: costBasis = Money(1000.00) + Money(240.00)\n= Money(1240.00)\nremainingToSell = ShareQuantity(2) − ShareQuantity(2)\n= ShareQuantity(0) ✓

== Finalize ==

Holding -> Holding: lots.removeIf(Lot::isEmpty)\n→ Lot #1 removed (0 remaining)

Holding -> Holding: proceeds = Price(150.00) × ShareQuantity(12)\n= Money(1800.00)

Holding -> Holding: SellResult.of(\n  proceeds = Money(1800.00),\n  costBasis = Money(1240.00))\nprofit = Money(1800.00) − Money(1240.00)\n= Money(560.00)

Holding --> Portfolio: SellResult(\nproceeds = Money(1800.00),\ncostBasis = Money(1240.00),\nprofit = Money(560.00))
deactivate Holding

Portfolio -> Portfolio: balance = balance.add(Money(1800.00))

Portfolio --> Service: SellResult
deactivate Portfolio
deactivate Service

note over Portfolio, Lot2
  **After the sell operation:**
  • Lot #1: **removed** (fully depleted)
  • Lot #2: 3 shares remaining @ 120.00
  • Portfolio balance: increased by Money(1800.00)
  • SellResult proves FIFO: costBasis = (10×100) + (2×120) = 1240.00
end note

@enduml
